<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0832 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book: analyzes more than forty compliance controversies raised bythe United States and the Soviet Union; examines all the major arms controlagreements: SALT I and II, the ABM Treaty, the Limited Test Ban Treaty,the Threshold Test Ban Treaty, the Biological Weapons Conventions, andthe Helsinki Final Act; reveals where both the United States and theSoviet Union have stretched reasonable interpretations of treaty provisions;and discusses how ambiguous treaty language can lead to unmerited accusationsof noncompliance.</TEXT></DOC>